message:
A list of Stalin's property made after several hours after his death:
"1. Notepad, grey leather cover;
2. Notebook, red leather cover; 
3. Personal notes made on separate sheets and tear-off sheets. Sixty-seven sheets numbered; 
4. Notebook with general notes, red cover; 
5. 5 smoking pipes with 4 boxes and special devices for them, tobacco. In the study of Comrade Stalin: books, desk accessories and souvenirs in the comrade Stalin's cabinet are not included. 

Bedroom and closet: 
6. 2 white colored tunics (Both have medals "Sickle and Hammer" of the Hero of Socialist Labour attached); 
7. 2 grey tunics; 
8. 2 dark-green colored kitels; 
9. 10 pants; 
...
A savings book was found in the bedroom with 900 rubles written in it."

#History #USSR
